===Etymology===
Derived from Arabic {{ARchar|[[صفة]]}} (''súffa'', [[sofa]], long seat made of stone or brick). The word may have entered European languages via Turkish or through the Moorish occupation of Spain.

===Pronunciation===
*sō'fə, /ˈsəʊfə/, /<tt>"s@Uf@</tt>/
*{{audio|en-us-sofa.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:[[Rhymes:English:-əʊfə|Rhymes: -əʊfə]]

===Noun===
'''sofa''' (plural: [[sofas]])

# An [[upholster]]ed seat, typically having sides and back, long enough to accommodate two or more people.

